theorem P1_iff_closure_subset_closure_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A ↔ closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1]
  constructor
  · intro hP1
    exact closure_mono hP1
  · intro hSubset
    intro x hxA
    have hx_cl : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) := subset_closure hxA
    have : x ∈ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := hSubset hx_cl
    simpa using this

theorem P1_implies_P1_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A → Topology.P1 (closure A) := by
  intro hP1
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1 ⊢
  -- Step 1: `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have h₁ : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
    have h₁' : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (closure (interior A)) := by
      exact
        (closure_mono
            (s := (A : Set X))
            (t := closure (interior A))
            hP1)
    simpa [closure_closure] using h₁'
  -- Step 2: `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
  have h₂ : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
    have hInt : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
      interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
    exact closure_mono hInt
  -- Combine the two inclusions.
  exact h₁.trans h₂

theorem P2_compl_of_isClosed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsClosed (A : Set X)) :
    Topology.P2 (Aᶜ) := by
  have hOpen : IsOpen ((Aᶜ) : Set X) := hA.isOpen_compl
  exact (Topology.isOpen_has_all_Ps (X := X) (A := (Aᶜ : Set X)) hOpen).2.1
